The Naleraq's harsh and pure secessionists are excluded from the new executive but also the other Greenland political forces, although with different shades, are favorable to self-determination, and is on the self-determination that Washington aims to bring the Arctic island into its orbit. "What we believe will happen is that the Greenlanders will choose, through self-determination, to become independent of Denmark, and from that moment, we will open a dialogue with the people of Greenland," Vance explained, "we do not think that the military force will ever be necessary, and since the people of Greenland is rational and good, I think we will be able to reach an agreement."
&nbsp;
