While Vance, accompanied by his wife Usha, met the troops stationed in the base, Donald Trump> reiterated the press that the US needed Greenland not for themselves but "for peace in the world, for international security". "If you look at the maritime routes, there are Chinese and Russian ships everywhere," said the President of the United States, "Greenland is very important for world peace, not for us but for peace in the world, and I believe that Denmark understands it, I believe that the European Union > understands it. And if they don't understand it, we'll have to explain it."
Vance also stressed the need to "stop the intrusion" of Russia> and, above all, of China> which is "very, very interested in this island", scenario in front of which "can not put the head under the snow". And this task, he added, cannot be done by Denmark, which "is not doing a good job, is not investing sufficiently in the population and security of Greenland."
