Responding to journalists' questions, Vance also answered questions about negotiation for the truce in Ukraine, which would be recording "incredible progress"; on the trade war with Canada, "which cannot win it" and, above all, on the '<a href="https://www.agi.it/estero/news/2025-03-26/scandalo-chat-signal-piani-guerra-the-atlantic-30613325/">case Signal</a>' which sees it involved in the first person. Vance was in fact among the high officials present in the chat where the attack plans were being discussed in Yemen and to which the editor of the magazine 'The Atlantic' was mistakenly added. >
The American vice president accused the media of covering the errors of the administration passed on the withdrawal in Afghanistan > and then attack the current one "for a chat on Signal" and then assured that "no one will be fired" for the clamorous escape of news. The Director for Homeland Security, Mike Waltz, considered responsible for gaffe, would therefore not be at risk. &nbsp;&nbsp;
